# HTML

This next table is good.

```{r html, eval = FALSE, results = "asis", echo = FALSE, message = FALSE}
library("tab")
library("xtable")
library("knitr")
#library("printr")

data(d)
d <- d[complete.cases(d), ]
glmfit1 <- glm(BMI ~ Age + Sex + Race + Group, data = d)
lintable <- tabglm(fit = glmfit1, columns = c("beta.se", "p"), 
                   format.xtable = TRUE)
lintable[4, 2] <- "--"
t1 <- xtable(lintable)
print(t1, sanitize.text.function = identity, type = "html")

```

What did yall think.

# Word

```{r word, eval = FALSE, results = "asis", echo = FALSE, message = FALSE}
library("tab")
library("xtable")
library("knitr")

data(d)
d <- d[complete.cases(d), ]
glmfit1 <- glm(BMI ~ Age + Sex + Race + Group, data = d)
lintable <- tabglm(fit = glmfit1, columns = c("beta.se", "p"))
kable(lintable)
```

